# Rust / Cargo
/target/
**/target/
# Flash-time builds use a separate CARGO_TARGET_DIR so the flash/non-flash
# feature sets don't thrash one cache; keep them out of git AND out of
# lint / ast-grep scans (generated build code would otherwise trip style rules).
/target-flash*/
# Note: Cargo.lock is tracked for reproducible builds in workspace with examples

# Rustfmt / Clippy / IDE noise
**/*.rs.bk

# Brainstorming session artifacts (visual companion)
.superpowers/

